  What is Digital Signage?Digital signage is a modern version of traditional signs or posters. The main difference is that we use web portal software to send visual content onto big flat TV screens that are connected to computers. It’s like having your OWN TV CHANNEL for less than the cost of a poster.So now you can throw-out all those old thumbtacks, because you will never have to hang another poster, EVER AGAINYou can see Digital Signage everywhere – in stores, malls, corporate towers, residential buildings and even museums. It uses technologies such as LCD, LED and Projection to display content in digital images, video, streaming media, and corporate information.MyMedia works as a Digital Signage Integrator, using all the tools and expertise you need to effectively create a solid communication channel.  How do we do it?In 2005, we started to work as a Toronto Digital Signage team for corporate initiatives across the city.  Since then, our Digital Signage team has grown to include New York City, providing us with the ability to scale large or small deployments. Our network of installers are situated in every major city in North America, proving we have the depth and breadth to reach multiple markets easily.Some of our locations:• Oakville, Ontario• Burlington, Ontario• Rockville, Maryland• Tucson, Arizona• Orlando, Florida• Cambridge, Massachusetts• Sparks, Nevada• Durham, North Carolina• Kirkland, WashingtonWe know how to make a solution run smoothly and successfully to minimize downtime. When a customized solution is necessary, we will tailor a solution that meets your specific requirements.Great service and convenience is our standard . With our turnkey services raging from: content development, installation, hardware configuration and software, we provide our clients with a total 360 degrees of service. In essence, we become your Digital Signage communication partner.Contact us today and STEP INTO THE NEW ERA OF COMMUNICATION!Toronto area: 905-232-7677Toll Free: 1-866-636-0636 ext 224 My Media - Digital Signage Toronto & New York Blog






