Editors' Note:
Download.com has chosen not to provide a direct-download link for this product and offers this page for informational purposes only.







Editors' Review+

                            by:
                
Download.com staff

                                    on September 03, 2013
                    



MyMedia is an image and video downloader and browser for iOS devices that integrates a number of useful tools to manage media files on your phone or iPad. The inclusion of a custom browser is nice and the media browser, while not as advanced as those in similar apps, is effective, allowing you to access and move through large volumes of audio, image, or video files on your phone, remotely.
When you set up MyMedia you will see a rundown of how the app works, complete with an outline of what it can do and what options you are given to work with the features of this app. The browser may look pared down, at first, but it uses many of the same features from Safari, combined with download tools that will move any media you encounter to your phone or tablet's library. You can then access these files, view them, move them to a cloud storage platform of your choosing, transfer them via Wi-Fi to iTunes, or delete them. Settings are also available to passcode lock your files or change how they are saved and backed up.
MyMedia ran smoothly in all of our tests, finding files, downloading them, and backing them up when we selected them. While the interface is cumbersome, at times, with some options hidden in unexpected places, the app is generally well made so you can find and access these files on the go, with ease.




 

