A MEDIA AGENCY BORN TO PERFORM
Mercury Media is a performance media agency with a heritage in direct response. Driving action isn’t just what we say we do. It’s the crucible that formed us. From our deep roots in DR, Mercury has grown into one of the leading independent performance-based marketing agencies in the country.
Our team of strategists works backward from what our clients need to achieve, then develops media strategies that relentlessly drive results. We craft objective omnichannel approaches that put our clients’ desired outcomes first, then we optimize for maximum impact and efficiency.
 We are Mercury Media






DRIVEN BYCOLLABORATION
We work with a roster of national and global brands who are just like us: diverse, multifaceted, and determined to create success through highly effective investments in media.


Nuwave Oven


Nuwave  develops products that promote efficiency and value while enhancing the quality of life. NuWave consistently surpasses customers’ expectations when it comes to reliability, efficiency and value. When it comes to product development, they go above and beyond. More than simply offering customers the best products at an unbeatable value, are dedicated  to developing a foundation of trust and dependability.



American Standard


For over 140 years, American Standard has led the way in developing innovative bathroom and kitchen products including high performance toilets, stylish faucets, and wellness products that have set and re-set the standards for living healthy, living responsibly, and living beautifully.



Dragon NaturallySpeaking


Dragon NaturallySpeaking (also known as Dragon for PC, or DNS),is a speech recognition software package developed by Dragon Systems of Newton, Massachusetts, and later acquired by Nuance Communications.  The software has three primary areas of functionality: dictation, text-to-speech and command input. The user is able to dictate and have speech transcribed as written text, have a document synthesized as an audio stream, or issue commands that are recognized as such by the program.



Omaha Steaks


We are Omaha Steaks, a fifth-generation, family-owned company with a passion for providing the finest in premium beef and gourmet foods for our family of customers. Our company originated in 1917, when father and son, J.J. and B.A. Simon, immigrants from Riga, Latvia, founded The Table Supply Meat Company, a small custom butcher shop in Omaha, Nebraska. The original company sold tender, premium beef to discerning restaurants, hotels and grocers.



The Wall Street Journal


The Wall Street Journal is leading newspaper with a special emphasis on business and economic news. The Journal primarily covers American economic and international business topics, and financial news and issues. Its name derives from Wall Street, located in New York City, which is the heart of the financial district; it has been printed continuously since its inception on July 8, 1889.



Waterpik


Waterpik, has been a leader in developing personal and oral health care products for the entire family since 1962. They have acquired many patents for their innovations, and Waterpik products are recognized for award-winning design and technology.



Lenox


Lenox is America's leading tabletop and giftware brand. Lenox shares a passion for design and style with those who love to entertain and celebrate with family and friends. Lenox fine china, crystal, flatware, giftware, home décor and tabletop products are timeless pieces that reflect superb quality and craftsmanship.



Guthy-Renker


Guthy-Renker, is the industry leading direct-response marketing company that sells products directly to consumers through infomercials, television ads, direct mail, telemarketing, spam mail, and the internet. Guthy-Renker has discovered and developed dozens of well-loved, high quality consumer products in the beauty, skincare, entertainment and wellness categories. Known for moving, award-winning productions and marketing campaigns featuring some of today’s leading celebrities, the Company has been credited with transforming the broadcast direct marketing industry.



Inogen


Inogen was founded based on our conviction that oxygen therapy technology was not keeping pace with the desired lifestyles of patients who depended on it to live longer, more fulfilling lives. Inogen is innovative oxygen.








